battle in Congress, President Clinton wants the federal government
to authorize $22 billion in bonds to build new schools and repair
old ones, issuing tax credits to those who buy them. The debate on
school construction also is being fueled by a 1996 federal report
that showed 60 percent of American schools need significant
repairs. (Monroe, Cox Washington Bureau)
