<SLUG> BC-BKN-RODMAN-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RODMAN WEIGHS LAKERS' OFFER 
</HEADLINE>
  (bl) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   A deal for Dennis Rodman to join the Los Angeles Lakers was
still in place Saturday, but the 37-year-old forward had not
decided whether to accept, a sports executive with knowledge of the
Lakers' plans said.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers were offering Rodman, the National Basketball
Association's seven-time rebounding champion and the league's most
flamboyant player, the veterans' minimum salary of $1 million _
prorated to about $600,000 for the lockout-shortened season.
</P>
<P>
   John Black, the Lakers' director of public relations, told The
Associated Press on Saturday: ``We have not signed him. We have
nothing to report.''
</P>
<P>
   If Rodman joined the Lakers, it could set in motion other roster
changes over the next month. The Lakers are prepared to send two
starters, Eddie Jones and Elden Campbell, to Charlotte for Glen
Rice, J.R. Reid and B.J. Armstrong. Rice is expected to miss the
first 20 to 25 games of the season while he recovers from elbow
surgery.  &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-02-13-99 1635EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
