<SLUG> BC-BOAT-AROUND-ALONE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DAMAGED YACHT SAILS ON SLOWLY
</HEADLINE>
   (jw) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Josh Hall, the British solo sailor whose yacht was dismasted in
heavy seas on Thursday night, was continuing to make slow progress
toward the Chatham Islands on Saturday under jury rig. Hall,
competing in the 1998-99 Around Alone race, is out of the
nine-month, 27,000-mile event.
</P>
<P>
   At last report, Hall was 201 miles from the islands and had
managed to cover only 46 miles toward his destination in the last
24 hours. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-02-13-99 1638EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
