<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-02-13 22:22 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4777 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKN-BARKLEY-REAX-HNS &LR;      02-13 0723
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-BARKLEY-REAX-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
Rockets seek a team adjustment
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; By JONATHAN FEIGEN &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; c. 1999, Houston Chronicle &LR;  &QL; 
The Rockets _ and all things considered, the world _ have one
Charles Barkley. They cannot insert Othella Harrington or anyone
else into Barkley's spot and expect them to rebound, pass and score
as Barkley has and with Barkley's style.
</P>
<P>
   They similarly will not seek a roster addition. Antoine Carr is
roughly two weeks away from coming back from his knee injury.
</P>
<P>
   Instead, the Rockets will adjust to losing Barkley for three to
four weeks after his arthroscopic knee surgery today. They will try
to do something else, hoping to do it well enough to make up for
what Barkley had done so well before his injury forced surgery.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's going to be tough,'' Rockets coach Rudy Tomjanovich said.
``We're just starting to get used to that chemistry. And Charles is
different than other players. He catches the ball in different
areas. It's going to be an adjustment.''
</P>
<P>
   Said Rockets forward Scottie Pippen: ``You can't calculate what
Charles brings to the team. Everything he does on the court doesn't
show on the stat sheet. It's going to be tough. He's been
rebounding the heck out of the ball. He's been scoring big for us.
It's going to be tough to bring back what Charles is doing, with
the intimidation factor he brings as well.''
</P>
<P>
   Harrington, though not necessarily the automatic replacement in
the starting lineup, surely will pick up many of the minutes.
Harrington is second in the NBA in field-goal percentage and runs
the floor well.
</P>
<P>
   But he does not draw the double teams Barkley exploits with his
passing and the Rockets use to key much of their offense. And those
plays are relatively low-risk, especially this early in a season
that began with little time for training camp.
</P>
<P>
   Instead of recapturing what Barkley brings, the Rockets likely
will look for something to take its place. Instead of getting easy
baskets when left open by defenses concentrating on Barkley inside,
the Rockets could look for easy baskets in transition to utilize
Harrington's speed.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have to come together as a team,'' Pippen said. ``I don't
think I have to alter my game in Charles' absence. `O' (Harrington)
brings a different style to our offensive game. It gives us the
opportunity to run the ball a little more; using his speed and
quickness to get early baskets should be great for us.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just hope everybody is up for the challenge. It's going to
be a big challenge for us. We have to start looking to create our
offense early on instead of going to a half-court game.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's great if we have Hakeem (Olajuwon) down there and he's
giving us some points down inside. But we have to look to get some
early baskets in our transition. That's where `O' is going to be
big for us.''
</P>
<P>
   Olajuwon also can have a larger role in the low post. But he
also said if the entire roster plays better it could make the
Rockets a stronger team in the long run.
</P>
<P>
   ``I have to step up,'' Olajuwon said. ``Everybody on the team
has to step up to compensate. That's the quality and the
characteristics of a championship team. You have a major player
out, but they still manage to find a way to win. That's what we
have to develop.''
</P>
<P>
   But with Barkley's injury, the concerns about the Rockets' age
are sure to surface. If the knock had been the team's key players
were too old to avoid injuries, Barkley's would seem a case in
point.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is an injury,'' Barkley said. ``This is not us breaking
down because we're old. I just got hurt. The doctor said it's just
a small little thing. Once it's fixed it's over with.''
</P>
<P>
   And Pippen has experience with an older team that did not suffer
the sort of injuries that prevented postseason success.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think there's any truth to that,'' Pippen said. ``I
played with the Chicago Bulls that were said to be an old team. The
old teams have more success. Injuries happen. Things just happen.
You can't say there's not going to be an injury. We happened to
lose an important piece to our puzzle.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think it's a great opportunity for this team to show we can
exist without Charles. We have to show we can exist without one of
our key players. I think we're ready for the challenge.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
